gularly, and consider myself relatively patriotic.  I love the United States of America, and want the best for it.  I also want the US, as a country, to behave in ways that are best for us and for the world.<br>
<br>
I also agree with most of what Taranna says.  So am I disloyal because I think Bush is an incompetent, and that his international policies are so haphazard as to border on the schizophrenic?  Because I think Bush is a shill for large corporations, particularly those in the petrochemicals industries?  <br>
<br>
Despite what Fox news and other political neanderthals spout, dissent is not disloyalty.  Indeed, I dislike the current administration, and its actions, not because I hate my country.  In fact, quite the opposite is true, I dislike Bush *because* I love my country, and I feel that his actions diminish both our reputation, and the fundamental freedoms our founding fathers held so dearly.<br>
<br>
If you want to make leader worship a litmus test for loyalty, then I'll suggest to you that a republic is the wrong form of government for you, sirs.  <br>
