As you hint at, I don't dislike Bush for the party he belongs to- I liked HW Bush and Reagan a lot.  If Herb Walker Bush ran from any party, he would have still been the best candidate for me- if GW Bush ran from any party with the same administration he has now, I wouldn't touch him with a 10 foot pole.  Powell and McCain are both staunch Republicans, but I think they would make far better Presidents than the current incumbent, or indeed John Kerry as he stands today.  My issues with Bush are his policies and their abject failure, not party politics.<br>
<br>
  You see what I mean by accountability and faith-based policies also.  I agree with you that faith is a fine thing on a personal level- but spreading Gospel in the name of policymaking that kills people is something the Ayatollahs in Iran do, it shouldn't be what an American president does.<br>
