Refute this, I dare you.  Using familial and political connections to get into a non-combatant unit is dodging, plain and simple.  Then, to blow the flight status paid for by the taxpayers by not getting a physical, and not drilling adequately to complete his obligation, he further dishonored those who actually did do their duty.<br>
<br>
Let's not also forget: in aptitude tests for flight, George Bush scored in the 25th percentile, yet still was selected for a highly contested Air National Guard slot. Bush's reserve unit included the son's of Sen. Lloyd Bentsen and Gov. John Connally, as well as several members of the Dallas Cowboys.  It was called the &quot;Champagne Unit.&quot;  Seeing a pattern here? No, of course not. <br>
<br>
Bush's reserve drill attendance is public record.  So is the composition of the list of those who got non-combat flight billets.  Instead of putting your fingers in your ears and screaming liberal bias, check it out.  Or were the officials keeping the reserve records in a big left wing conspiracy?  Maybe Anthony Zinni is a bleeding-heart liberal senior general from the Marine Corps too?  It's nice when you can ignore facts to make one's own Weltanschauung the reality.<br>
<br>
Ever served in the military?  Do you know what happens to normal people in the National Guard and reserves who don't complete their drilling obligations?  <br>
<br>
&quot;faith driven&quot;<br>
Out of his own mouth. <br>
<br>
former drunk President<br>
By his own admission, Bush spent from age 16-41 controlled by alcohol. Arrested for DUI. blah blah blah. Again, all either his own admission or public record.<br>
<br>
Inflammatory or not, the above characterization of Bush is exactly factually accurate. <br>
